inn1.comm: what a start first up! Azhar Ali is gone, and it has taken a beauty to get him. This one pitches on length outside off and leaves him late, Azhar, who is camping back, is squared up as he pokes at that with the edge accepted gleefully by Denesh Ramdin. Umpire Ahsan Raza took a while, but the right decision has been made in the end.
angles it a touch ahead of good length on off stump from wide of the crease, defended solidly by Babar Azam
too full outside off at 141kph, squeezed down to third man to get off the mark
neat touch. Overpitched outside off, driven firmly but straight to extra cover

width on offer, Sharjeel chases that one but can't reach out. Umpire thinks it was far too wide outside off, and he's right. Good take by Ramdin diving to his left and taking that in front of first slip
too straight and on the pads, flicked neatly to deep midwicket

saved by a thick inside edge.  The length ball jagged back in a long way from outside off, he poked outside the line and somehow got some bat on it. For a moment, there was a possibility of the ball sneaking through the gap between bat and pad.
nips back in from middle, tucked to short midwicket
stays back inside the crease to a delivery he could have played forward, opens the bat face late to bunt that good length delivery to point

delightful straight drive. The key was to not hit the ball too hard, and the ball simply flew off the blade. Not much feet movement, but the bat came down nicely to caress that ball. Lovely timing, the kind of shots you'll never be bored of watching. Nothing wrong with the delivery either
slight inward movement from middle and leg, defended
hops back to punch that off the back foot to backward point
slants a length ball across, whipped across the line to midwicket
close to a wide, but he's lucky to get away. Short and wide, he's flirting with that marker there, left alone by Azam
beaten by a peach. Looked to drive on the up, but was clearly late on the shot. The ball held its line after pitching at length outside off. Sharp too, 142kph.
too full, he shapes to drive but can't get underneath it, squeezed to cover
firm push back down the pitch, Gabriel stops it on his follow-through
this one's flicked neatly to the right of mid-on for an easy single
this is much better, lands it a touch ahead of length on middle, Sharjeel stays inside the crease, perhaps because he's uncertain. Pushes it to cover
pokes outside the line of the length ball to get a thick inside edge onto the pad
stays on the back foot and defends to the man at cover point. Not much bounce, going by what we've seen so far
buffet ball as Geoff Boycott would call it. Overpitched on the pads, flicked behind square on the leg side, the boundary rider does well to cut that off
looks to draw him forward by floating it full outside off, not much movement on it, however. Azam lets it go
once again he isn't committed fully forward as he defends that full-length delivery on off stump, defended to point
solidly behind the line of the ball this time, played with straight bat towards mid-off. Steady over that from the West Indies captain
punches a back of length delivery on middle to midwicket
full on middle, squeezed to the off side. Looked like he picked it late, but jammed down on time to keep that yorker out
another yorker-length delivery but outside the line of the stumps, defended again

wow, you can pay big money to watch shots like those. All timing and grace from Sharjeel, who leans forward, extends his arms and crashes that ball on the up between cover and point. Class written all over it. He's got a good bat too! Nothing wrong with the delivery, mind you.
overcompensates by pitching it up on the pads, flicked onto the leg side, deep square leg runs to his right to cut that off

briefly, just briefly, there was a shout of 'catch' but mid-off needed to be 10 feet tall to have any chance of getting a hand on that. Once again, this was too full, and Sharjeel went at that with the intention of hitting it up and over. Got enough bat on it too. Pakistan getting a move-on
stands tall and punches one off the back foot to point
incoming length delivery on off stump from wide of the crease, defended to point
wrists an incoming delivery behind square leg, lazy effort from Narine allows an extra run

drifting into the pads, worked away towards long leg where Gabriel was late to react. Excellent running to get back for the second. The fielder recovered well to fire a good throw, but a second's indecision earlier cost West Indies a run
looks to force that off the back foot behind point, gets a bottom edge that races past the slip fielder towards third man
can't pick the gap this time. It was short and angling away, he mistimes an attempted punch to cover
back of a length delivery on off, pushed to cover
length ball on middle, worked across the line to midwicket for a quick single
hint of width outside off and he's hammered that behind point. Third man had no chance. Picking the length early was the key, and he did that nice and early before giving it a good thwack
on the pads, flicked to deep square leg for an easy single
floats it full on middle from wide of the crease, defended back down the pitch

wrong line, wrong length and put away without breaking into a sweat. Drifts a length ball into the pads, Azam does well to tickle that with the angle past short fine leg. Once it crosses the infield, it can get extremely difficult to even try and stop the ball. Easy runs these
stays inside the crease and bunts a back of length delivery to the off side
pokes half-heartedly at an away-going delivery, didn't miss the edge by much
gives it a solid thump off the front foot, but straight to backward point
drops the ball into the off side towards cover and scoots across for a quick single, Azam was off the blocks just as Shajeel looked up.  Eye contact did the trick there
driven firmly, Holder didn't have enough time to bend and put his boot out to deflect that ball towards midwicket
back of length delivery on off stump, defended to cover
stays inside the crease and dabs the length ball to cover
opens the face of the bat late to steer the away-going delivery to point
just a hint of width on offer, he opens the bat face late to glide the ball behind point. Superb timing
get behind the line to defend that length ball to the off side

false stroke, and is lucky to get away with it this time.  Goes for an across-the-line slog, ends up slicing it down toward third man. Would have been down the lap of the man there, but fortunately there was no one
no half-measures! Did the last delivery have any effect on him? It didn't look like. Sees it in his swinging arc, and he simply gives it a big swing to clear wide long-on. Muscular hit
gets forward and caresses the full ball to cover

this is as good as it can get. Overpitched on middle and he drills that down the ground. The ball had already raced past the bowler before he could put his foot down on the follow-through. Magnificent timing
steers the slow off-cutter to backward point

another flat hit, and he's just managed to clear long-on. Gets underneath the line and lofts him effortlessly over the infield. It was too full and begging to be dispatched. Sharjeel is in his zone here. He had to fetch it from off stump, but the balance and timing was superb
slower one on middle, tapped to cover
length ball on the pads, tucked around the corner, short fine leg comes around towards square leg to stop that
starts off with a very full delivery, smacked down the ground
good length outside off, backs away and steers past point, third man gathers it
good length outside off, no turn, punched away to sweeper cover and they jog across for a single
pitches it up on the stumps this time and Azam whips it through the vacant midwicket region
comes forward and looks to tap it to the off side but the ball goes away to square leg off the inside edge
fuller ball, close to off, pushed back to the bowler
flighted on the stumps, driven to covers
backs away to cut outside of but it keeps a tad low and the batsman is beaten
not much turn outside off, slaps it away to covers
harmless delivery outside off, doesn't turn much, waits for it before opening the face of his bat and steering it to third man
tucked off the pads to midwicket where the fielder puts in the dive to stop the ball, so no run there
nudges it away to square leg and momentarily thinks of a quick second run but they decide against it
drifting in and raps the batsman on the pads as he comes forward to defend but it's sliding down lwg
coms down the track to take it on the full before pushing it back to the bowler
generously flighted, driven crisply through extra cover, cut off in the deep
no turn outside off, waits for it before gently steering it away to point
thinks of going big down the ground but changes his mind after seeing the length and ends up nudging it to sweeper cover
fuller ball, driven to wide long-off
comes forward and dabs it to point
sharp turn! Sharjeel hangs on the backfoot and doesn't move his feet as he pokes at it, spins past the outside edge
shorter ball, pulled comfortably pulled away between deep midwicket and long-on
stands tall on the backfoot and punches it to long-on
width on offer, cuts late to point
pitched up, Sharjeel swings hard across the line from the crease and comfortably beats long-on
eased with the spin to long-off

another swipe across the line and he can't middle it this time. Fetched it from way outside off and tried to slog it. But it was too wide and not full enough to connect with the slog either. Gets a healthy leading edge that is snaffled at short third man
defended on the front foot back to the bowler
given a lot of flight on off, comes forward and eases it to wide long-off

flighted outside off and drifting in. Azam comes forward and looks to defend but is rapped on the pads. Confident appeal for lbw from the bowler but the question is if there was any bat involved. Holder asks for the review and replays show that it brushed the pad before hitting the bat. S Ravi, the third umpire, has a long, hard look at it. Hawk-eye shows that the ball would have clipped the bails on middle stump, so the umpire's call remains. No more reviews for West Indies.
waits on the backfoot and pushes it to mid-on

pushed through quicker and Malik prods forward but the ball hisses past the outside edge. It didn't turn as much. Ramdin takes the bails off in a jiffy and they go upstairs to check for the stumping. Malik did drag his foot out but just about manages to get it back
very full on the stumps, gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
sprays it slightly wide and Malik slaps it through point. Sweeper cover darts across and fields the ball
fuller but still wide outside off, presses forward and punch-drives it to sweeper cover
defended back to the bowler
flighted on the stumps, eased down to long-on
comes forward and smothers the spin as he defends to the off side
width on offer, backs away and slaps through point, sweeper cover gets around it
wide again and shorter as well, Azam cuts it straight to sweeper cover
presses forward and pushes it to the right of the fielder at sweeper cover
pitched up outside off, driven on the front foot back to the bowler who dives to his left to stop the ball
punched down to long-off for a single
offers width outside off, cut away
pitched up on the stumps, eased down to long-on
fuller and straighter, worked down the ground to long-on

outside edge taken at first slip. It was the carrom ball from Narine and Malik presses forward and is looking to play for the off-spin. Gets a thick outside edge that is well-taken by Benn who gets down quickly to pouch it
tucked to midwicket
advances down the track and fends it off to covers
worked to long-off
gets down to sweep early but it's fired wide outside off, gets a glove to it before the ball hits the back thigh
comes down the track looking to work it to the off side but the ball escapes to midwicket off the inside edge
generously flighted outside off, swipes hard but can't beat cover
flighted and drifting in, gently defends it back to the bowler
pushed through quicker and drifting in, stays in the crease and punches it to the left of the bowler who sticks his hand out and gathers it
bowls it flatter on the stumps, shifts back and punches it back to the bowler

played very late, waits for it to come on before opening the face of his bat, the ball goes past the diving first slip fielder towards the third man fence. Carlos Brathwaite gives it a good chase and the ball slows down as it approaches the boundary. Manages to pull the ball back but they go upstairs to see if he has made contact with any part of the boundary. He's done that cleanly
width on offer again and he opens the face of his bat again. Gives the shot some power this time and the ball beats Brathwaite to the third man boundary
comes forward and takes this from outside off and wrists it to long-on
flighted and way outside off, gets a long way across and taps it to point after reaching out for it. It's cut off there
fires it down the leg side, the batsman makes no contact as he tries to glance it. The bails are taken off but his foot never came off
driven down to long-on

stumping chance missed. Big moment in the match?  Sarfraz chips down the track to play it past midwicket, but ended up yorking himself. The keeper may have been unsighted as the ball drifted back in a touch. Opportunity nonetheless
gets forward and eases it to the off side
steps out and plays it back towards the bowler again
makes a bit of room and eases the short ball wide of point for an easy single
punched off the back foot to cover
straightens after pitching on middle, he lunges forward and blocks
starts off a new spell accurately, pushed back down the pitch towards the bowler, who half-stops it. Pressure released as they steal a run

super strike down the ground. Angles a full ball on middle from wide of the crease, Babar drills a straight drive over the bowler's head. The umpire had to take evasive action too. Excellent punch in the stroke brought about by strong forearms.
chops a full ball outside off to the keeper. It was too full and close for him to try and glide that behind point
shapes to cut but was late on the shot. There's some fizz off the deck for Gabriel
bangs a short ball into middle from wide of the crease, he gets on top of the bounce and eases it down to third man
firm push, but straight to the cover fielder
generously tossed up on middle from around the stumps, he stretches out a long way to defend it back to the bowler
drifts into middle, inside-edges an attempted drive back to Benn again
quicker delivery outside off, driven through the line to sweeper cover
stretches forward to negate the dip, turns it with the angle to short midwicket for a quick single
slow turn from middle, Azam covers the line and stabs it to the off side
steps out but can't get to the pitch of the ball, blocks
opens the bat face late to steer the ball into the gap at square third man, Carlos runs around to his right and then dishes a dive to stop the ball.  Saved two runs for his side
not much feet movement. Glued to the crease as he pushes outside the line of the length ball, gets an inside edge onto the pad
lovely on-drive, showed the full face of the bat. It was travelling, but Kraigg Brathwaite does well to cut that off at mid-on with a tumbling stop
straightens after landing it at length on middle, pushed back to the bowler
neatly steered down to Pollard at third man, it wasn't all that short but he still managed to play it effectively
steered down to third man for an easy single to end the over
attempts a flick, the ball deflects off the pad to short cover
steps out and defends a quicker delivery back to the bowler
goes back deep into the crease, opens up the off side and then plays the cut very late to get it behind point
on the shorter side again, once again Kraigg Brathwaite has a lot of work to do. Runs across from deep cover to deep point to save two runs for the side
eases a tossed up delivery back to the bowler

sixth ODI fifty  and this has been a lovely little knock so far. Yes, he had the rub of the green going his way early on, especially with the lbw shout, but he's played well since. The in-drifter has been tucked behind square on the leg side quite comfortably to bring up the landmark
class written all over it. Mid-on was in the circle, which meant he had no chance to stop that delightful straight drive. He showed the full face of the bat to time it so sweetly
slow leg-cutter on off, chopped down to third man
Benn misfields at point  to concede a run. It was squeezed with an opened bat face, he dived over that delivery
good stop at point, redeems himself this time with a diving stop to his left
bowls it full on off, drilled to mid-off, couldn't pick the gap
swivels back and pulls, but can't generate the kind of power he was looking for. On the bounce to deep midwicket. Looked like a tired shot
rolls his fingers over the ball and floats it full on middle, turned to midwicket
driven firmly but straight to cover. He's having a look at the bat handle. The bat face turned in his hand, but he still managed to hit it hard
back of length on middle and leg, turned round the corner to deep square leg
plays a proper square drive through the vacant point region towards the boundary rider
slower and fuller on off stump, he taps it gently into the off side and pinches a run that may have not been possible had the fielder at cover been a little more alert

drills a low full toss into the cover boundary. He was standing a couple of paces outside the crease perhaps for this very reason. Generated good power on that as he made contact. No one moved in the off side ring.

Brathwaite had three stumps to aim at, at the bowler's end. He missed to reprieve Azam in the end.  Sarfraz dabbed it to the leg side and called for a run, only to turn his back on the partner. Brathwaite did well to run down the pitch and then collect the ball, turn back. Did everything right, except hit the stumps
glides it down to third man for an easy single
cuts, but straight to short third man
drifting into the pads, and he's simply helped it over square leg. The flick of the wrists did the trick there. He always intended to hit it up and over, and executed it perfectly
gets half-forward and defends the leg-cutter gently
firm push, but straight to cover
too full and angling into the pads, turned towards deep backward square leg
not much room to work with, pushed back to the bowler
drops it with soft hands towards point and gently ambles across for a run. Mindn you, he didn't hit it beyond the 30-yard ring
clever stuff, once again a simple dab towards the man running in from cover
leans forward and dabs it toward point for another easy single.
tapped gently towards cover, this time the fielder is quick to get in to prevent that
angles an incoming length delivery towards point
forced off the front foot to Narine at cover. He wanted to pinch the gap between cover and long-off
worked across the line wide of midwicket for a quick single
sweeps and misses. Looked to get outside the line of the stumps to fetch the stroke, but couldn't get underneath the delivery
this time he sweeps, but hits it straight to short fine leg
slower leg-cutter outside off, looks to stay inside the crease and run it down to third man but is beaten by the late deviation
full and angling in, lifts it with the angle to deep midwicket
full toss outside off that dips late, Sarfaraz comes down and awkwardly swipes at it. Gets it to backward square leg but not off the middle of the bat
backs away and slaps it to point
backs away and exposes the stumps but Pollard over-adjusts and fires it way down the leg side. It;s so wide that the keeper can't collect it despite putting in the dive
full and holding its line outside off, driven gently through extra cover
cuts his pace down and bowls it at the pads, clipped away to deep midwicket
full outside off and very slow, sqeezed out to point
advances down the track and pulls this length ball with the angle to deep midwicket
looks to open the face of his bat and guide it down to third man but picks backward point
length ball, angling in, tucks off the hips to backward square leg and takes off for a quick single. Throw is at the non-striker's end but it doesn't hit anything
beaten by a lack of pace. Tries to open the face of his bat and run it down to third man but the ball keeps low and there is no pace on it
pulled to deep midwicket
very full ball, swipes and gets it away to the region between deep midwicket and long-on. Two fielders converge and the long-on fielder puts his boot to it to stop it from reaching the boundary
dabs it wide of point for a quick single
backs away and makes room but the bowler follows him and bowls it full, he wears it on the pads as he misses the flick
too predictable. It's too full and on the pads, no pace again but Azam was ready for it. Gets down on one knee and slogs powerfully as the ball goes clean over the deep midwicket boundary
rolls his fingers over the seam and bowls a slower one that is angled down leg, tucked away to deep backward square leg comfortably. This is now Azam's highest ODI score
good length on middle and leg, tucked away to midwicket
full and outside off, stabs it towards third man after opening the face of his bat
fetches it from outside off and sweeps to backward square leg
turns in after landing on middle, eased down to long-on
width on offer and that's a gift for the batsman. Just has to pick the gap at point which Sarfaraz does well as the ball goes between point and gully to the third man fence
not as full this time but another sweep shot this time and the ball is fielded at backward square leg
runs it down to wide long-on
full and outside off, swept to deep backward square leg
walks across the stumps and Holder fires it wide outside off, tapped away to point for a single
full and outside off, driven through covers, man in position at sweeper cover, so they get only one
full and on the fourth or fifth stump channel, driven towards deep point
gently dabs it down to third man for another easy single
cutter that lands too short outside off, pulled away to deep fine leg for a brace

comes down the track and looks to slog across the line. It was another slower ball and Sarfaraz fetches it from way outside off, loses balance as he plays the shot and gets an under edge that is held by the wicketkeeper. Clear noise and the umpire raises his finger. Replays show that the front foot landing may have gone awry. They try a couple of angles and it becomes clear that Holder has just about got his foot behind the line. A centimetre further outside and it would have been a no-ball. They check if the catch was clean as it was snaffled quite low. All clear in the end as the giant screen spells out 'OUT'
fires it on middle stump channel, not much turn, eased down the ground to long-on
fligted on off, gets forward and punches confidently. The fielder at cover dives but the ball sneaks past him
pushed wide of cover
width on offer, moves back slightly and cuts, finds backward point
comes forward and pushes it to long-on
gives it a lot of air outside off, driven crisply but straight to cover
slower ball and wide outside off, Azam reaches out but can't make contact
bangs it in and there is enough width on offer for Azam to comfortably to deep midwicket. Quietly marches on to 96 now
short ball, quite close to off, so Rizwan jumps up to ride the bounce before steering it down to third man
another slower ball outside off, drills it into the ground as he opens the face of his bat, the ball goes away towards third man
short and angling in, pulled away to deep backward square leg
full and outside off, pushed through extra cover for another single
full and outside off, driven firmly to covers where the fielder makes a diving save
stays in the crease to this length ball and stabs it to the right of the bowler
swept around the corner behind square on the leg side
slightly short in length, Azam punches it to sweeper cover to raise his maiden international century. Gets a good applause from the Sharjah crowd and he soaks it in
runs it through cover-point for a single
opens the face of his bat and looks to slap it away but can't beat the fielder at point
gives it too much flight and bowls a full toss which is driven to wide long-off
tries to get down on one knee and slog it powerfully over the leg side, but it is bowled slower through the air and the batsman is beaten by the lack of pace
uppishly works it to long-off but the ball lands well before the fielder there
full and outside off, gets down on a knee and sweeps and the ball races through the vacant square leg region
steers it to short third man
full and wide, drills it to extra cover

total chaos!. Flat and quick on middle stumps, tries to open the face of his bat and get it to third man. There is a short third man in place and the striker sets off for a run. He is hesitant and can't make his mind up. Azam at the non-striker's end sends him back and he scampers back but it's a direct hit and he is caught short of his crease
pushed straight back to the bowler
slightly floats it up on the stumps, Imad pushes it to long-off to get off the mark
floated up on middle and leg, uses the angle to work it down to long-on

waits for it and tucks it to square leg, it's vacant there so they call for two. Two fielders converge on the ball and one of them picks it up and fires a throw at the non-striker's end but it misses the stumps
comes forward to defend and gets an outside edge as the ball goes away towards third man
in the slot and he's simply slapped that disdainfully into the gap between deep point and wide long-off. Split the gap perfectly
slows it down this time, tosses it over the batsman's eyeline, he looks to drill it down but gets hit on the pad off an inside edge towards square leg
worked with the spin towards deep midwicket for an easy single
there's no holding back this time. Gently tossed up, he got to the pitch of the ball and then hammered it over long-on. Excellent use of the bottom hand, what power in that stroke
turned with the angle towards square leg
pushed through quicker on middle, worked round the corner towards midwicket
sharp turn from outside off, Imad shapes to loft it over cover but lets it go in the end
pushed back down to long-off for an easy single
steered straight to Pollard at backward point

wow, that's a delightful hit and he's launching them on demand. Once again there's enough flight on this one for him to swing with the turn. Down on one knee and boom, sailed over the ropes and landed on the tent-roof at deep midwicket
drops it into the off side with soft hands for a quick single
gets a good stride forward and blocks

those are the kind of catches you really don't plan for. This one was drilled down the ground, the flick of the wrists, generated the power. It was destined to sail over wide long-on, but Kieron Pollard, lurking around the ropes, had other ideas. He ran around the ropes and then stretched full-length to his right to use every inch of his height to his advantage. Then plucked his hand out and was airborne as the ball got stuck in. Amazingly, he had the presence of mind to realise he was going over the ropes, and then gently lobbed the ball back, got back into the field of play, settled himself underneath to take the catch. Imagine he completed all of this in a matter of five seconds. Simply outstanding. He's done this time and again in the IPL, so it doesn't really come as a surprise. Super stuff.
eased down to long-on for an easy single
tucked off his hip towards square leg
shapes to pull but can't get enough bat on it, flat hit to midwicket
looks to glide it behind square but ends up playing it towards cover
slapped off the front foot but straight to the fielder at the edge of the circle at cover
eases the full-length delivery wide of mid-off for an esy single
crunching sound of the blade as he slapped that length ball, but straight to the cover fielder

sliced over third man.  No ball for the height, so it will be a free-hit.  Looks to bowl a yorker, but it slips out. It turned out to be a waist-high full toss wide outside off, there was room to swing his arms and he made enough contact to get the ball up and over behind square

another full toss, but this was well below the waist, which effectively took out the no-ball threat. The batsman made room to open up the off side and then carve it into the deep cover region. Excellent improvisation. His mind is ticking so efficiently, picking his spots and hitting them well
they steal a leg-bye as he gets a deflection off the pad while looking to whip it past square leg
gets a thick inside-edge on the drive down to long-on
drops it into the off side gently to pinch a quick single
whipped into the gap at deep square leg, Narine had some work to do, they made the second quite easily
looks to cramp him for room by angling one in from around the stumps, he gets a deflection towards short fine
full-length outside off, squeezed to the man at the edge of the circle at cover
full on the pads, flicked to deep midwicket
slower delivery outside off, he is beaten in an attempt to run it down to third man. Not sure why he'd try that, considering he had to force the pace
punched to a gingerly looking Benn at cover for a quick single
starts off with a shocker down leg side, all Nawaz needed to do to get a boundary was a faint tickle, but missed it. Good take by Ramdin
banged in on length around off stump, dabbed to cover for a quick single
plays a short-arm jab to midwicket, didn't get the kind of power he would have liked on that
muscles a flat hit, but finds Narine at midwicket. Once again the angle ensured there wasn't much room for him to play a full-blooded pull
drilled down the ground to mid-off, a direct hit from Holder at the non-striker's end and Nawaz would have been walking back
poor delivery, drifting down leg, whipped off his hip to deep fine leg. That was bowled at 144 clicks
goes for another pull, but can't get it up and over Narine at midwicket. He was cramped for room as well, so couldn't time it as well as he would have liked. The bat face turned in his hand too
looks to flick it behind square but is early into the stroke, the ball deflects off the pad to the off side
back-of-the-hand slower delivery on the pads, turned behind square leg

full, slow and straight on middle, he went for a biff across the line but was through with the stroke even before the ball got to him. By the time the bat came down, the ball had already hit the middle of middle stump. Imad Wasim has been dismissed, finally. That can put an end to all talks of his average for the time being. Excellent ball from Carlos. As angry and annoyed as West Indies have been since coming back onto the field, they've been that much more intense in their effort on the field too.

hits the stumps direct at the non-striker's end as Wahab looks to scamper a leg-bye. But the bat gets stuck into the crease just as he plonks it in. At the same point, it also slips out of his hand and Wahab's foot is in the air as the bails come off. Third umpire has been called for, and he's made the right decision. Carlos missed a run-out chance earlier, but has somewhat made up for it with this super throw. Poor from Wahab, no excuses for not grounding his bat properly, he had all the time in the world to sort that in the nick of time
bowls a slower delivery on off stump, Amir gets forward and blocks
squeezed wide of cover to get off the mark
gets a thick inside edge to deep square as he looks to swing across the line
hops back to angle a short of length delivery on middle towards third man

he's hit that into Abu Dhabi. Wow, what a hit! This was a length ball on middle, he cleared his front leg and swung across the line to clear long-on with minimum fuss. The free swing of the bat did the trick, the ball made a lovely sound as it flew off the blade.
pulled, but straight to Narine at the edge of the circle at midwicket
backs away and carves a yorker-length delivery outside off towards square third man
slogged, but couldn't get underneath the full-length delivery, down to long-on

good strike, but straight down the throat of the captain at deep midwicket. Slowed it down nicely as he saw the batsman trying to wind up, he went through with the swing and holed out to the lone ban in the boundary. Quit a comeback this has been by West Indies after the break. And to think of it, they weren't keen to come out and play because of ongoing issues with the floodlights

squeezed back down the ground, Carlos dives to his left to stop that, but his failure to transfer the ball from left to right before firing a throw cost him some time in his quest to effect a run-out at the striker's end, saved a run though
yorker-length on middle, somehow manages to dig that out
squeezed to the man at extra cover as they scamper through for a run
slower ball outside off, he swung early and only managed to get one off the bottom of the bat
squeezed down the ground to long-on where Pollard came charging in and collected the ball where mid-on would be stationed

inn2.comm: full delivery drifting into the pads, worked to long-on
tucked off the back foot to midwicket to get off the mark
gets half a stride in to defend an arm ball drifting into middle
turned with the angle to square leg where Shoaib Malik runs across to his left to stop that
worked down to long-on with a straight bat. No turn, just drift so far for Imad Wasim
solidly behind the line of the ball as he blocks
late swing back into Charles, who is hit high on the thigh pad as he looks to nurdle it towards square leg
floats a full delivery across Kraigg. There is no swing back in this time, left alone
easy pickings, short and sliding into middle and leg, flicked uppishly to deep backward square leg
gets a thick inside edge to square leg. He looked to force that up and over cover
nips away off the seam from outside off, flirting with the wide line, the umpire thinks it was a legitimate delivery
lets go an away swinger that pitched on middle and off.
too full on the pads, tucked wide of midwicket
appeal for caught behind, a stifled one, but there was no bat on it. The ball swerved back in to deflect to the keeper off the pad
hit on the pad as he looks to work it across the line towards square leg, but the ball would have missed the stumps
gets a good stride forward and blocks the incoming delivery
turns it around the corner to short fine for a quick single

read the angle, saw the ball tossed up and then blasted that over deep midwicket. That should get him going. If you're going to swing that hard, ensure you're up to the pitch of the ball. Charles certainly did that on this occasion
late on the cut, the ball had already shaved past the outside edge before his feet could move
play and a miss. Feet stuck to the crease as he pokes at the away-going delivery
hops back into the crease to bunt a short of length delivery to cover
his technique is being tested here. Once again he is rooted to the crease in anticipation of a short ball perhaps, Amir floats this full and across to beat an ungainly poke
this is outstanding bowling from Amir. Once again gets this to move away off the seam from the good length area on middle, beaten!
covers the line of that delivery and defends to midwicket
bowls it down the leg side, tries to flick but gets it on the pad
goes for a wild slog but gets it off the inside edge to square leg. That was very close
tucked behind square on the leg side
tries to get it away to the leg side but misses and is struck on the pad
rapped on the pads as the batsman tries to flick and misses but that was heading down leg, seems like. Pakistan don't opt for the review
nudges it to midwicket on the front foot
teases him with a slower ball that is angled away outside off, Charles tentatively goes after it and is beaten
tucked off the pads to square leg
good length, pushed across, defends it to covers, no run there
length ball outside off, punches it on the front foot to extra cover, man at cover runs across and puts in the dive to cut it off
tucked off the pads to backward square leg

beaten. Beautifully bowled, you want to see more of those kind of deliveries. Fires a tempter that is full and outside off, Brathwaite goes after it and somewhat walks into the shot as he looks to play it on the front foot, the ball shoots past the outside edge
pushed through quicker, tucks it between midwicket and wide long-on
turns it off the pads behind square

awkward slog but gets him four. It was floated up on the stumps and Charles gets down on one knee and swipes at it. Gets it somewhat uppishly through square leg. No timing but the shot has enough to carry to the boundary
works it to backward point
defended back to the bowler
nudged to midwicket
short of a length, outside off, pulled to deep square leg, fielder at deep midwicket runs across and cuts it off
good length on leg stump, tucked to midwicket
good length angling in, inside-edges the forward push to the pads

edged and gone. Short of a length ball outside off, angled in to the right-hander before it straightens late. Charles sticks his bat out and pokes at it, gets an outside edge. Clear sound as the ball goes to the wicketkeeper
fuller ball, clipped away to the leg side
defended back towards the bowler
fuller length outside off, comes forward and carefully defends to covers
good length outside off, comes on to the front foot and defends to mid-on
worked to covers

good length on off, looks to defend but gets an inside edge as the ball goes to square leg. They scamper through for a quick single and there is a chance of a run out but the throw at the striker's end isn't the best
angling away outside off, Bravo is caught between playing and leaving, decides to withdraw his bat late but unwittingly hits the ball as it goes to point
angling in on middle and leg, tucked away
good length outside off, gets a neat stride forward and defends it to the off side
good length ball, slightly shapes away late, Bravo defends from the crease and the ball goes off the outside half of the bat back to the bowler
fuller and on the pads, clips it away but finds midwicket
back of a length outside off, moving away late, punched from the crease to covers
short of a length outside off, stays in the crease and stabs it to cover-point. No one there but the point fielder darts across and fields it. No run there
angles his bat and runs it down to third man for a single and retains strike

fires it full and on the pads, Bravo looks to tuck it away but gets an inside edge on to the pads before the ball rolls away to the leg side. Brathwaite at the non-striker's end wants a single but Bravo sends him back as the bowler hares forward in his follow-through to pick up the ball
short of a length, tucked behind square
good length outside off, taps it to the right of mid-on
fired on off, defended
full ball outside off, goes with hard hands as he looks to drive and the ball goes off the inside edge past the stumps to backward square leg
fuller and on off, Bravo gently pushes it from the crease towards mid-off, Hasan Ali springs across in his follow-through to stop the ball
good length on off, blocked to covers
fuller and outside off, uses his wrists and fetches it from outside off, gives it some power so the ball goes uppishly to mid-on, lands safely before the fielder there though
crisply driven, full and just a tad outside off, gets a neat stride forward and creams it through extra cover
clips it off the pads to the right of mid-on
on a length and wide, gets forward and gently drives it to the left of sweeper cover who runs across and fields it
tucked to the on side, mid-on runs across and gathers it
good length on off, defended

tires to open the face of his bat and pays the price. It was slightly short of a length and quite close to off stump. Brathwaite did the mistake of trying to run it down to third man. It wasn't quite wide enough to do that and he gets an outside edge that is held by the wicketkeeper
back of a length outside off, drops it just to the left of point and takes off for a quick single
length ball, angled across, played to sweeper cover
short of a length outside off, offers a straight bat as he looks to defend and chops it into the ground as the ball goes behind the stumps
defended back towards the bowler
back of a length outside off, slight late movement, Bravo stays in the crease and slaps it to deep point
short ball, gets up on his toes to ride the bounce before trying to nudge to the on side
width on offer, steered wide of point
good length, angling in, blocked solidly back to the bowler
exposes his stumps as he gives himself room before running it down to point
short ball, pulled to deep midwicket
bowls it fuller this time and Samuels comes forward and pushes it to mid-off
tucked to midwicket
slower ball, comes forward looking to drive but is beaten by the lack of pace
short and angling away, goes through with the pull shot and makes no contact
full and wide, gets forward and pushes to to covers
pitched outside leg, looks to tuck it away but gets a leading edge
full and on leg, clipped off the toes to backward square leg
flighted outside off, gets forward and gently taps it towards cover-point, the fielder at point runs across and cuts it off
shorter in length, stays in the crease and punches it to extra cover
tucked to midwicket off the pads
gives it a lot of flight outside off, driven along the carpet to long-off
bowls it full on the stumps, Bravo defends to the on side
flighted and on the stumps, tucked to the leg side
flighted on middle and leg, pushed firmly back to the bowler
full and outside off, driven past covers to wide long-off
short ball, tries to slap it but gets an inside edge

flatter ball that goes through straight. Bravo was looking to make room and slap it away. But the ball wasn't wide enough. And it spins back in sharply and cramps him for room. Keeps a tad low as well and Bravo makes no connection as the ball crashes into the stumps
tries to nudge it to the leg side but gets a leading edge
stays in the crease and punches it away to long-off
gives it too much flight and bowls a low full toss that is pushed gently down to long-on
flighted, full and on the leg stump, the ball goes off the outer half of the bat to covers as Samuels looks to dab it to the leg side
short and wide, slaps it away to backward point
played back to the bowler
straightens after landing on middle and off, slapped away to covers
flighted on leg stump, tries to work it away to the leg side but inside-edges it to the pads
eased down to long-on
driven through covers where the fielder's dive goes in vain. Wide long-off runs across and cuts it off
flighted on leg, defended on the front foot to mid-on
width on offer, Samuels' eyes light up and he opens up his arms as he looks to slap it but can't beat point

flighted from outside off, gets it to drift away and Samuels pushes at it without moving his feet away. It turns the other way and he doesn't account for that, gets an outside edge through the vacant slip cordon
full and wide, drills it through cover-point and point for a brace
waits for it before cutting it away but can't beat the cover fielder
bowls in on leg and it doesn't turn at all, goes down the leg side
gives it a lot of air and Samuels drives it straight to cover
flighted and angled in from around the stumps, gets forward and pushes it back to the bowler
runs in down to long-on to keep the strike
fired outside off, the ball breaks away sharply, eased to point
drifts into middle from around the stumps, punched straight to midwicket
gets a thick inside edge as he looks to work that down to long-on, a misfield by Imad at midwicket gives them an easy single
gets a good stride forward to defend
this one fizzes through, Ramdin is late on the shot but somehow manages to get his bat down on time to keep that out
misses out on a full toss, flicks it straight to midwicket
looks to fire it in to cramp Samuels for room, slips it down leg, good take by the keeper
that should ease the pressure and the escalating asking rate a bit. Didn't get to the pitch as he stepped out but hit through the line with a straight bat to clear long-on with ease. Top shot
turned wide of square leg for an easy single
gets under the flight and works it with the spin to deep midwicket
steps out but can't get underneath the flight, bunts it to cover this time
backs away and crunches that into the gap between cover and point, good placement. There seems to be more intent now

that's even bigger. That's the Samuels we know. He can be deadly dangerous if he gets his eye in, and it looks like he has today. Nicely tossed up, Samuels stepped out early and this time he got to the pitch before blasting that into the second tier over the long-on boundary.
too full on middle and leg, squeezed down to long-on
flicked with the angle to long-on again
drifts into middle, he looks to tap it gently and scoot a single towards midwicket, but the fielder is alert to the possibility
appeal for lbw, but it looks like he was hit outside the line of the stumps. There was an inside-edge too. He also kicked the ball away as it was rolling back
pushed through quicker on middle, blocked

there was a cry of anguish from Sarfraz as Imad bowled that. Too full outside off, Ramdin makes a bit of room and slaps it into the deep extra cover boundary. He knew it was a bad ball the moment it was released. West Indies getting a move on
drops it into the off side with soft hands as they pinch a quick single

Azhar Ali has the last laugh, but the ball has pounded into his hands and he's in some pain, which he won't mind because Pakistan have broken what was looking like a threatening partnership. This was gently tossed up outside off, Ramdin went hard at that and picked the bones out of that, except he found the cover fielder instead of going over. The ball banged Azhar's chest and then lodged between his hands as he recovered to complete the catch.
gets forward and stabs it to the off side, wanted a run but Samuels wasn't keen
steps out and forces it down the ground to long-off
slow turn from middle, pushed to backward point
bowls a fast'ish in-drifter on middle, defended to the off side

for a moment it looked like he'd dragged it from outside off and that it came off the bottom, but he still managed to hit it 20 yards back into the stands at deep midwicket. He was also looking to hit it a lot straighter than he managed to in the end. Runs nonetheless
slides back in, keeps a touch low as well, pushed back to the bowler
fired into middle and leg, tucked wide of square leg. The result of that six is that he's pulled his length back
steps out and drives it inside-out to long-off
gets to the pitch of the ball and works it down to long-on for an easy single
deceived in flight, so he ends up dabbing it gently. He was initially lining up to go inside-out over cover

it was just a matter of time, you felt, before Pollard holed out and that's been proved right. There's a hint of grip and turn on this one, Pollard was looking to go over cover, but ended up slicing it towards deep point where Sharjeel took a straightforward catch. That he didn't get to the pitch of the ball may have also influenced the final outcome as the ball skewed up. West Indies in disarray now.
driven with the spin to long-off to bring up the 100 for West Indies
drifts back in to take a thick inside edge as he attempts to drive, rolls to midwicket
gets half-forward and punches it to cover
makes a bit of room and forces that off the back foot to sweeper cover
straightens after pitching on middle and off, Holder uses the depth of the crease to play it back down the pitch
nearly had his man. This one swerves back in to cramp Samuels for room as he shaped to cut, fortunately he managed to make the late adjustment and bunt it back down the pitch
worked with the angle towards deep midwicket
drift back in to hit him on the pad, but the ball was angling down leg. The impact was marginally on leg, but remember, the ball still had to travel a long way
punched back to the bowler

through the gate this time, and it's not surprising at all. The lbw shout was eerily similar, except the ball didn't sneak through. No such luck this time. A familiar mode of dismissal for Imad. This one drifts back in again, almost like a late inswinger, Holder looks to go inside-out but plays down the wrong line to hear the sound of the ball hitting the stumps. The collapse continues
bowls the arm-ball this time, Carlos squeezes it out to point
worked down to long on for an easy single
gets the bat well in front of the pad to smother the  spin
gets the edge but rolls along the ground to gully. Once again, there's drift and turn
too full and sliding into the pads, flicked to mid-on
nurdled behind square on the leg side
slow turn from outside off, bunted to point and calls 'no' immediately
beaten in his attempt to play an ambitious reverse sweep to a quicker delivery. Fortunately for Carlos, it was outside off and kept low too
gets a good stride forward and blocks
deflects off the pad to short fine as he tooks to tickle it towards the leg side
gets onto the front foot and defends the incoming delivery to the leg side
eased back past the bowler to long-on, Carlos jogs across for the single
grips and turns square, Samuels looks to drive but in the end rocks back to punch that to point
bangs a length ball in on middle, defended back down the pitch

that clears the straight boundary with ease. Carlos had decided he was going big even before the bowler delivered. Stayed deep inside the crease to take it on the full and swing it over the ropes. He teed off like a golfer on that occasion. The big broad blade and the muscles of his are a deadly combination
whipped off his hip towards midwicket for an easy single
glides it down to third man with an angled bat
beats him with one that pitches and straightens. Did it reverse in? Carlos played outside the line assuming it would leave him

'catch' was the call, but it was a question of who. Length ball, he didn't get underneath that by any means but simply went through with a straight bat, only to get the desired elevation and distance. Long-on fielder was just a mere spectator.
gets forward to defend that tossed up delivery to cover
steps out and drills that into the gap at extra cover. Superb use of the feet. Got underneath the flight and opened the bat face late to crash that
squared up as he jabs at that, scoots across for a single as point runs in a fires a wayward throw to the keeper

that is as good as it gets for a left-arm spinner. Carlos plays for the one that straightens, but this time it spun away sharply to beat his forward prod and hit off stump. Nawaz has bowled a ripper and that should give him so much confidence
slow turn back into middle and leg, pushed to midwicket
steps out and hammers a flat hit over long-off. Once again nowhere near the pitch but he swung through. Oh, these modern bats. How they sail to make the bowler look like dust at times
chops it down to third man for a single
short of a length outside off, jumps up before tapping it to point
back of a length, steered to backward point
short and outside off, looks to angle his bat and run it down to third man but is beaten
bouncer on the stumps, Narine awkwardly gets under it
defended off the backfoot to covers
flighted on leg, advances down and pushes it firmly to long-on
pushed through quicker and flatter, turns in sharply from middle and leg, tucked behind square
backs away to make room before slapping it away to backward point
gets on to the front foot and negotiates it against the turn to midwicket
worked away to sweeper cover and they jog the single
pushed through quicker and straighter, stays in the crease and defends to point

done in by pace. Good length ball, angled in. It is delivered with some serious pace and Samuels has little time to react to it. The ball hits him on the pad first before crashing into the stumps. He had backed away a long way to make room for himself and ended up exposing the stumps and the bowler followed him with a pacy delivery
short and wide, slapped away to backward point
very full outside off, drills it out to covers
full delivery delivered at good pace, 144kmph, Benn gets his bat down as he tries to squeeze it out but can't make any contact, just ends up making hard contact with the turf
good length outside off, Benn uses the pace on that delivery and makes use of the width before crisply driving it through extra cover
changes the angle and comes from around the wicket, bowls it full and outside off, it is squeezed out to point
spin and bounce from the good length area, tucked with the turn to fine leg

full and on the pads, gets down on a knee and sweeps but gets a top edge. The ball runs away to the fine leg boundary but Azam, the centurion, sprints across and puts in a desperate dive to just pull it back

hammered. It was tossed and pitched up outside off, slower through the air as well. Benn's eyes light up and he picks it up from outside off and gives it a good thump to send it back over the bowler's head through long-on
works it down to long-off
this one's even bigger. It was slower and flighted outside off. Narine comes down the track and heaves it clean over long-on. The ball goes deep into the stands

shouts of catch it but it lands short of the man at deep midwicket. Makes the adjustment in length after the twin sixes and drags his length back. Narine pulls uppishly and the ball goes on the bounce to the fielder
short and pushed across the left-hander, Narine looks to pull and gets a top edge as the ball runs down to third man where it is fielded
follows it up with a pacy bouncer that is superbly directed. Benn has to take evasive action and bends down hastily, takes his eyes off the ball too and his glasses come off as he reacts to that ball

superbly set up. Unsettled him with a short ball that had slightly unnerved Benn and follows it up with a yorker. Benn has no answer to that and the ball crashes into the stumps. But, hang on! Oh, dear! Wahab has overstepped. How nicely he had set up Benn. He deserved that wicket, but well, now he has to try again. Looks extremely tight as the camera zooms in on the crease and the foot has landed on the line
clears the front leg and tries to swipe across the line to the free hit delivery. It was on a length and angled away nicely. Benn can't reach it and the ball goes to the wicketkeeper
goes for the blockhole again but not quite there. It's still very full and is hurled at 149kmph, Benn manages to nudge it away to backward square leg
short ball but Narine is waiting for it. Picks the length up early and brings out the pull shot. The ball goes clean over midwicket

another short ball hurled at a similar angle and the same response from the batsman. Narine isn't hassled at all as he clears his front leg and pulls again. But he gets a top edge on it this time and the ball goes past the long-on boundary
fuller ball, gets an inside edge to midwicket

slower ball, Narine doesn't pick up the drop in pace and skies a catch to deep midwicket. It was hurled full and Narine set himself up to go big over the leg side. He gets some solid elevation on it and the ball stays up for a long time. Imad Wasim has enough time to settle under it at deep midwicket and takes it

yorker that hits him on the pad, Benn jams his bat down but is rapped on the pads. Appeal for lbw but that pitched outside leg and would have missed the stumps as well. Hit him flush on the right boot
makes room and slaps it away to deep backward point
full and wide outside off, swings very hard at it and doesn't make contact
another fuller ball, drills it down to mid-on
full and outside off, pushed back to the bowler
gives it too much flight and bowls a full toss, Gabriel attempts a big slog but it's too slow and he can't make good connection, gets it to midwicket on the bounce
flatter ball, tucked behind square
flatter ball on the stumps, defends and the ball goes to the leg side, thinks of the single but decides against it
flatter again and short in length also. Benn shapes up for a pull but inside-edges it to his leg
goes for the pull again but it isn't short enough, he can only miscue it to long-on on the bounce
fired on the leg stump, goes for the big slog but can't make any decent connection, inside-edges it to the pads
short of a length outside off, flat-bats it to mid-on where Nawaz dives to make the save. Jars his knee into the turf and hurts himself in the process
teases him with a fuller ball on the fourth or fifth stump channel, Gabriel responds with a big swipe across the line and doesn't connect
slower ball does it. Good length and Hasan rolled his fingers over the seam. Gabriel doesn't move his feet and tentatively sticks his bat out. The ball keeps a bit low and goes through the gate
